        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 22 at 4:50PM MDT by NWS Albuquerque NM</headline>
        <description>At 450 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a line of strong
thunderstorms extending from 6 miles northeast of Logan to 9 miles
north of Nara Visa, moving northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Nara Visa.

The potential exists for over 1 inch of rainfall from these storms.
</description>
        <instruction>Heavy rains from severe thunderstorms can produce sudden and
dangerous flows in arroyos, ditches and over low water crossings. Do
not attempt to drive through areas where water covers the roadway.</instruction>
